nodes.text: Level 1995 was a level of the city-planet Coruscant located below Level 1996. One area of the Level produced humming noises and strange lights, both of which could be perceived from a catwalk on the level above. Shortly after the destruction of the planet Alderaan, an Imperial Stormtrooper was thrown from a catwalk in Level 1996 by a Herglic criminal, and the trooper fell to his death in the depths of Level 1995.
Level 1995 first appeared in "One Thousand Levels Down", a short story written by Alexander Freed and published in Star Wars Insider 151 in 2014.
